    "body": "Thanks @mattsse for the information.\r\n\r\nI've tested and sending either `anvil_stopImpersonatingAccount` or `hardhat_stopImpersonatingAccount` works.\r\n\r\nFor anyone else looking at this, be aware that `hardhat_stopImpersonatingAccount` does not work with the Hardhat network so if your tests run against Hardhat or a local Anvil node you'll need to add an if condition to only run `hardhat_stopImpersonatingAccount` against Anvil. For example, the following will work if you have defined `anvil` as a network in your Hardhat config.\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nimport { ethers, network } from \"hardhat\"\r\n\r\nif (network.name === \"anvil\") {\r\n    await network.provider.request({\r\n        method: \"hardhat_stopImpersonatingAccount\",\r\n        params: [USDC.address],\r\n    })\r\n}\r\n```",
